  <!-- ─── SECTION 2: AI BASICS ─── -->
  <section id="what-ai">
    <div class="section-head">
      <h2><span class="icon">🧠</span> AI basics — in plain finance English</h2>
      <div class="sub">Simple language first, buzzwords last</div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card span-6">
        <h3>What is AI?</h3>
        <p><strong>Artificial intelligence</strong> is software designed to perform tasks that normally require language understanding, pattern recognition, or decision support.</p>
        <p><strong>Generative AI</strong> creates content such as summaries, tables, drafts, slide structures, or explanations. It predicts outputs based on patterns and the context you give it. That is why <em>context matters so much</em>.</p>
        <div class="callout green">
          <strong>🧾 Finance translation:</strong> Treat AI as a very fast assistant for drafting, summarising, comparing and structuring — <strong>never</strong> as the final owner of accounting judgement.
        </div>
        <div class="trainer-voice">
          "AI is like an incredibly fast intern who has read everything on the internet but has never actually closed a month-end. Useful? Absolutely. Trustworthy without review? Never."
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card span-6">
        <h3>📖 Core concepts — the cheat sheet</h3>
        <table>
          <tr><th>Term</th><th>Plain explanation</th><th>Finance example</th></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Prompt</strong></td><td>Your instruction to the AI</td><td>"Draft a month‑end variance note using this table."</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Context</strong></td><td>The information AI can use</td><td>Entity, period, currency, data table, audience</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Grounding</strong></td><td>Using files, emails, policy text or meetings as sources</td><td>Answer references an internal policy or workbook</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Hallucination</strong></td><td>A confident but <em>unsupported</em> answer</td><td>Invented GL code, policy rule or tax treatment 🚨</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Review</strong></td><td>The human checkpoint</td><td>Controller checks logic, numbers and wording before use ✅</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

