      <div class="sub">The useful part isn't "AI" — it's <em>where</em> the AI sits</div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card span-8">
        <p>Your activation email states that <strong>Microsoft 365 Copilot brings generative AI directly into Microsoft 365 apps</strong> — including Outlook, Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Teams and Edge — and that the licence provides <strong>secure, enterprise‑grade access</strong> aligned with Korn Ferry's standards for data protection and responsible use.</p>
        <p class="source">Source: Your M365 Copilot activation email, lines 14–18.</p>
        <div class="spotlight">
          <div class="spot">
            <strong>🎯 Why finance should care:</strong> The work already lives in Microsoft 365 — mail threads, Excel files, Word memos, PowerPoint packs and Teams recaps. The closer the assistant is to the work, the less copy‑paste and context loss you get.
