  <!-- ─── SECTION 4: CHATBOT vs AGENTIC ─── -->
  <section id="differences">
    <div class="section-head">
      <h2><span class="icon">⚡</span> Chatbot vs Work‑context Copilot vs Agentic Copilot</h2>
      <div class="sub">This is the section most teams remember — because it changes how you think about the tool</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <table>
        <tr><th style="width:18%">Mode</th><th style="width:26%">What it feels like</th><th style="width:30%">Where it helps</th><th style="width:26%">Review requirement</th></tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>💬 Simple chatbot</strong></td>
          <td>You type a question and receive an answer or draft.</td>
          <td>Explaining a concept, rewriting text, structuring a first draft.</td>
          <td>Always review. No unsupported confidential data in unapproved tools.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>🏢 M365 Copilot<br>(work context)</strong></td>
          <td>You ask, and the assistant can work with <em>permitted</em> emails, files, meetings and chats in Microsoft 365.</td>
          <td>Summarising what someone sent/shared, catching up on meetings, drafting from a document or thread.<br><span class="source">Source: Explore M365 Copilot email, lines 28–35, 61–67 and 101–107.</span></td>
          <td>Review sources and output; permissions still matter.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
