        <h3>🔬 The universal prompt formula</h3>
        <div class="prompt-block">Act as [role].
Task: [what you want].
Context: [entity, period, currency, audience, source table/document].
Constraints: [do not invent numbers, cite sources, flag assumptions, ask questions if missing data].
Output format: [email / table / memo / slide outline / checklist].</div>

        <h3 style="margin-top:20px">🎯 Three ready‑to‑use finance prompts</h3>

        <div class="prompt-block">1) Variance commentary
Act as a finance controller.
Using the table below, draft a concise month‑end variance commentary for MENA leadership.
Focus on movements over 10% or USD 25k.
Do not invent explanations; where the driver is unclear, write a question for the local finance manager.
Output: executive summary, top drivers, risks, follow‑up questions.</div>

        <div class="prompt-block">2) Audit request tracker
Act as an audit coordinator.
Convert the below request into a tracker with columns: request, entity, owner, due date, evidence needed, status, risk if delayed.
Flag unclear items and draft a polite follow‑up email.</div>

        <div class="prompt-block">3) Policy Q&A
Act as a careful accounting policy assistant.
Answer the question using only the policy extract provided.
If the extract is insufficient, say what is missing and suggest what needs confirmation.
